
[1]haste

   HASTE, n.

   1. Celerity of motion; speed; swiftness; dispatch; expedition; applied
   only to voluntary beings, as men and other animals; never to other
   bodies. We never say, a ball flies with haste.

   The king's business required haste. l Sam.21.

   2. Sudden excitement of passion; quickness; precipitance; vehemence.

   I said in my haste, all men are liars. Ps.116.

   3. The state of being urged or pressed by business; as, I am in great
   haste.

                                    HASTE
